ork offers a necessary counterbalance to a wider cultural neuromania that seeks out purely neural explanations for human behaviors as varied as reading, economics, empathy, and racism. Building on recent scholarship, Tougaw's evenhanded account will be an original contribution to the growing field of neuroscience and literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 20. Sep 2019) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Semiotics & Theory.2bisacsh1 aLeDoux, Joseph E.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2018z978311063899840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300235609423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/doc/cover/9780300235609.jpg  a978-3-11-063899-8  YUP eBook Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles